<figureCitation box="[330,419,1324,1351]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–96" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[166,1404,385,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1435,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 91–96. Male genitalia, median lobe, group dispar: 91. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 92. A. dispar, 93. A. insuturatus, 94. A. schwarzi, 95. A. taeniopygus and 96. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm and 500 ʯm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557907/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 96</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityName="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2019" box="[442,991,1324,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goianiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[442,710,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Amblycerus goianiensis</emphasis>
Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1003,1068,1325,1351]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1003,1068,1325,1351]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar externally and in relation to genitalia to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[407,565,1361,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[407,565,1361,1387]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the frontoclypeal suture distinct (indistinct in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[1373,1390,1361,1387]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), cervical boss with four setae (three setae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[772,929,1397,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[772,789,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[803,929,1397,1422]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the last ventrite almost twice as long as the ventrite IV (almost as long as ventrite IV in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[649,806,1433,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[649,666,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[680,806,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), internal sac of male genitalia in the apical region with a subtriangular sclerites (with a pair of ovoid sclerites in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[803,962,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[803,820,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[836,962,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), unpaired median subtrapezoidal sclerite (unpaired wishbone sclerite in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[496,654,1505,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[496,513,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[528,654,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
