</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1288,2035]" box="[199,1054,1576,1603]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,599,1576,1603]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Integument color (
<figureCitation box="[419,507,1576,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1656,1681]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,186,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Dorsal, group dispar: 9. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 10. A. dispar, 11. A. insuturatus, 12. A. schwarzi, 13. A. taeniopygus and 14. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557875/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[520,549,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[562,591,1576,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,184,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,174,1727]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Pygidium, group dispar: 78. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 79. A. dispar, 80. A. insuturatus, 81. A. schwarzi, 82. A. taeniopygus and 83. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557901/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">83</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Body red, except by light red antennae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1288,2035]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,595,1612,1639]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Vestiture (
<figureCitation box="[323,412,1612,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1656,1681]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,186,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Dorsal, group dispar: 9. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 10. A. dispar, 11. A. insuturatus, 12. A. schwarzi, 13. A. taeniopygus and 14. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557875/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[427,456,1612,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–27" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[326,1290,214,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[195,1392,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 22–27. Head, group dispar: 22. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 23. A. dispar, 24. A. insuturatus, 25. A. schwarzi, 26. A. taeniopygus, 27. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557881/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">27</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[470,499,1612,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[514,543,1612,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–53" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,453,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,445,1862]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 48–53. Pronotum, group dispar: 48. Amblycerus crassipunctatus. 49. A. dispar. 50. A. insuturatus. 51. A. schwarzi. 52. A. taeniopygus and 53. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557893/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[557,586,1612,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,184,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,174,1727]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Pygidium, group dispar: 78. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 79. A. dispar, 80. A. insuturatus, 81. A. schwarzi, 82. A. taeniopygus and 83. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557901/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">83</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Body covered with orange setae. Pronotum and elytra uniformly orange. Scutellum light yellow. Pygidium with median stripe of light yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1288,2035]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,153,719]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,1684,1711]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[279,363,1684,1711]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–27" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[326,1290,214,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[195,1392,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 22–27. Head, group dispar: 22. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 23. A. dispar, 24. A. insuturatus, 25. A. schwarzi, 26. A. taeniopygus, 27. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557881/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Frons covered with fine and moderately dense coarse punctures; without frontal carina. Eyes distant from each other anteriorly, ocular index: 3.0; ocular 
<emphasis box="[815,873,1721,1746]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">sinus</emphasis>
: 1.3. Postocular lobe 0.3 times the eye length. Antennae reaching anterior margin of hindcoxae; serrated from antennomeres 4–10; antennomere 7 about 1.4 longer than wide, last antennomere subelliptic. Frontoclypeal suture distinct. Clypeus covered with fine and moderately coarse punctures except by a narrow apical area. Labrum with few fine punctures on basal margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Prothorax (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 48–53" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,453,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,445,1862]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 48–53. Pronotum, group dispar: 48. Amblycerus crassipunctatus. 49. A. dispar. 50. A. insuturatus. 51. A. schwarzi. 52. A. taeniopygus and 53. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557893/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Pronotum trapezoidal with lateral margins slightly curved, covered laterally by coarse and dense punctures (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,1900,1927]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–53" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,453,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,445,1862]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 48–53. Pronotum, group dispar: 48. Amblycerus crassipunctatus. 49. A. dispar. 50. A. insuturatus. 51. A. schwarzi. 52. A. taeniopygus and 53. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557893/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
); lateral carina almost reaching the posterior margin of pronotum; cervical boss with four setae; cervical sulcus conspicuous behind eyes. Prosternal process longer than anterior coxae, gently arched between coxae and slightly constricted between coxae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[546,1010,1972,1999]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Meso- and metathorax (
<figureCitation box="[827,914,1972,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1656,1681]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,186,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Dorsal, group dispar: 9. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 10. A. dispar, 11. A. insuturatus, 12. A. schwarzi, 13. A. taeniopygus and 14. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557875/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[925,954,1972,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">40</figureCitation>
, 70).
</emphasis>
Scutellum about 1.5 longer than wide, tridentate in apical margin, median tooth longer than the lateral ones (Fig. 70). Elytra with striae strongly impressed, all free apically (
<figureCitation box="[339,422,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1656,1681]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,186,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Dorsal, group dispar: 9. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 10. A. dispar, 11. A. insuturatus, 12. A. schwarzi, 13. A. taeniopygus and 14. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557875/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Metepisternum with moderately coarse and sparse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1217,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); metepisternal sulcus with transverse axis gently oblique; the longitudinal axis about half the length of metepisternum. Metaventrite not prominent in lateral view, without punctures and with median sulcus longer than a half the lenght of metaventrite (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Metacoxae with coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[656,741,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Hindtibia with lateral spur about twice the length of median spur (
<figureCitation box="[216,303,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,598,296,323]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[457,546,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Figs 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[561,590,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,184,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,174,1727]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Pygidium, group dispar: 78. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 79. A. dispar, 80. A. insuturatus, 81. A. schwarzi, 82. A. taeniopygus and 83. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557901/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">83</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Ventrites without moderately coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1243,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[242,1369,227,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[190,1397,181,1925]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Lateral. group dispar: 35. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 36. A. dispar, 37. A. insuturatus, 38. A. schwarzi, 39. A. taeniopygus and 40. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); last ventrite almost twice as long as the ventrite IV. Pygidium with apical margin rounded and with dense and moderately coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[275,359,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,184,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,174,1727]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Pygidium, group dispar: 78. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 79. A. dispar, 80. A. insuturatus, 81. A. schwarzi, 82. A. taeniopygus and 83. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557901/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,153,719]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,539,404,431]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[386,474,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–96" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[166,1404,385,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1435,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 91–96. Male genitalia, median lobe, group dispar: 91. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 92. A. dispar, 93. A. insuturatus, 94. A. schwarzi, 95. A. taeniopygus and 96. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm and 500 ʯm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557907/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Figs 96</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[488,531,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–102" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,193,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1435,174,1872]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 97–102. Male genitalia, tegmen, group dispar: 97. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 98. A. dispar, 99. A. insuturatus, 100. A. schwarzi, 101. A. taeniopygus and 102. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">102</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Median lobe of male genitalia about 4.2 times times as long as its greatest width at apical region (
<figureCitation box="[385,470,441,468]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–96" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[166,1404,385,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1435,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 91–96. Male genitalia, median lobe, group dispar: 91. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 92. A. dispar, 93. A. insuturatus, 94. A. schwarzi, 95. A. taeniopygus and 96. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm and 500 ʯm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557907/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Ventral valve with lateral margins almost straight and acuminate apex. Dorsal valve subtriangular, with lateral margins almost straight, rounded apically. Internal sac in the apical region with a pair of hollow, ovoid, tuberculate sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[590,675,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–96" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[166,1404,385,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1435,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 91–96. Male genitalia, median lobe, group dispar: 91. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 92. A. dispar, 93. A. insuturatus, 94. A. schwarzi, 95. A. taeniopygus and 96. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm and 500 ʯm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557907/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Median region with a pair of blades serrate at lateral margin; with unpaired wishbone sclerite. Tegmen with moderate, rounded, emargination between the enlarged lateral lobes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 97–102" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,193,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1435,174,1872]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 97–102. Male genitalia, tegmen, group dispar: 97. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 98. A. dispar, 99. A. insuturatus, 100. A. schwarzi, 101. A. taeniopygus and 102. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557909/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[217,304,585,611]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
